The Compression Book — Licensing
=================================

This repository contains two kinds of material under two different licenses.

1. THE BOOK CONTENT — prose, figures, diagrams, and the typeset book
   (everything under chapters/, the .typ chapter sources, the built website in
   web/site/, and the PDFs) — is licensed under:

       Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)

   The Compression Book © 2026 Alexandre Betry is licensed under CC BY 4.0.
   You are free to share and adapt the material for any purpose, even
   commercially, provided you give appropriate credit.
   Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
   Summary:   https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

2. THE SOURCE CODE — the build tooling and all program code, including
   build_site.py, lib.typ, web.typ, and every Python code listing and the
   `tinyzip` project source that appears in the book — is licensed under the
   MIT License (see LICENSE-CODE).

If you redistribute or adapt the book, attribute it as:
   "The Compression Book by Alexandre Betry (CC BY 4.0)".
